          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The samples were mounted on either side of a",
                "thin aluminum partition in the common cathode of a",
                "back-to-back gridded ion chamber. For the fission",
                "counting the chamber was operated at low pressure to",
                "permit complete discrimination between fission and",
                "alpha pulses."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "RVAL",
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " If isotopically pure samples of Pu239",
                "and Pu240 are available, the ratio of the",
                "alpha-disintegration rates and the published ratio of",
                "the alpha-decay half-lives would give the ratio of",
                "the masses of the samples. The ratio of the fission",
                "rates in these samples, when irradiated in the same",
                "neutron flux, would then give the ratio of the",
                "fission cross sections. The accuracy would be limited",
                "to the accuracy with which the ratio of the",
                "alpha-decay half-lives is known."
              ]
            }
          ],
